                            <comment id="13703787" author="b4hand" created="Tue, 9 Jul 2013 21:05:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patches look reasonable to me, but I don&apos;t understand the relationship between the &quot;thrift2&quot; versus the normal &quot;thrift&quot; server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using CDH4 and the log messages appear to be coming from the &quot;thrift&quot; server not the &quot;thrift2&quot; one, so selfishly, I&apos;d like to see the &quot;thrift&quot; one fixed first. I&apos;m using the 0.9.0 thrift compiler and accessing it via Ruby and Python.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13704499" author="larsgeorge" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2013 12:32:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=b4hand&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;b4hand&quot;&gt;Brandon Forehand&lt;/a&gt;, yeah, I am working on Thrift 2 right now, but can apply the same to Thrift 1 for you. Going forward, Thrift 2 will be the Thrift version I am supporting, not sure about Thrift 1 then. Also, I am going to propose to deprecate Thrift 1 once I am done with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8818&quot; title=&quot;[thrift2] Update Thrift2 to supersede Thrift1 and equal REST&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-8818&quot;&gt;HBASE-8818&lt;/a&gt;. I&apos;ll update &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8695&quot; title=&quot;The HBase thrift service ignores XML configuration&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-8695&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-8695&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for you soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
